## Iteration loop — target 100% clean ontology by default

### Context
The generation loop used `score_threshold=70` and `stop_on_no_critical=True`,
meaning it accepted an ontology with minor warnings (P2.x / P3.x) as "done"
as long as no P1.x logical issues existed. Users expected the final ontology
to have zero warnings.

### Changes
1. `src/agents/agent_owl_generator/engine.py`
   - `_DEFAULT_SCORE_THRESHOLD`: 70 → **100** (only converge when score = 100 = no warnings)
   - `_DEFAULT_STOP_ON_NO_CRITICAL`: True → **False** (minor warnings still require fixing)
   - `_DEFAULT_MAX_FIX_ROUNDS`: 3 → **5** (more attempts to reach clean state)

### Modified files
- src/agents/agent_owl_generator/engine.py

### Test result
37 passed, 12 skipped — all green

