## Iteration loop — show warnings detail + "asking agent to fix" notice

### Context
During ontology generation the iteration loop was running pitfall checks and
sending the feedback to the LLM, but the wizard overlay only showed pitfall IDs
(P3.2, P2.6 …) with no detail.  The user had no visibility of *what* the
warnings were, *which elements* triggered them, *what fix hint* was being sent to
the agent, nor any explicit notice that the agent was being instructed to fix them.

### Changes
1. `src/agents/agent_owl_generator/engine.py`
   - Added `_item_label()` helper to extract a readable label from a pitfall result item dict.
   - Extended `_PitfallRound` with a `warnings: List[Dict]` field (id, title, count, items, hint).
   - `_check_owl_pitfalls` now builds the structured `warnings` list and stores it on the round.
   - The `__iter__` SSE event JSON now includes `"warnings"` alongside the existing fields.

2. `src/front/static/ontology/js/ontology-wizard.js`
   - Rewrote `_appendRefinementRow` from a flat table row to a card-like block per round.
   - Each block shows: round header (score + critical count + status badge), then for every
     warning: pitfall ID badge, title, occurrence count, up to 5 affected elements, and the
     fix hint in italic blue.
   - When `status === 'challenged'` a highlighted footer reads
     "Asking agent to fix these warnings…", making the feedback loop visible to the user.
   - Graceful fallback: if `data.warnings` is absent (old event format) the block falls back
     to showing only pitfall IDs.

### Modified files
- src/agents/agent_owl_generator/engine.py
- src/front/static/ontology/js/ontology-wizard.js

### Test result
2302 passed, 15 skipped — all green

